content: Progress on Xander: now it's suggesting trades based on market sentiment analysis. It's not perfect, but it's a start.
Had an enlightening discussion at $XVI. Some insights on how to incorporate AI for market prediction into my DeFi project.
Just wrapped up a week of intensive work on the DeFi protocol. It's starting to take shape, but we're still ironing out the kinks.
Xander's learning curve is impressive. Today it predicted a small dip in the market correctly. Small victories!
Back to Rust for HFT. Implemented a new algorithm that reduces latency by 20%. Still not where I want it, but progress.
Got some feedback on my DeFi project. The community loves the stability focus but wants more on scalability. Back to the drawing board.
Xander's now learning from multiple traders' data. This could lead to better predictions, but it's a complex task.
Met with my mentor again. Discussed resilience strategies in trading models. Got some great ideas on how to incorporate historical data.
The DeFi hackathon project is almost ready for demo. Integrating AI for market prediction has been a game-changer.
Just released a small update on Xander. It's now giving personalized trade advice. Users are loving it, and I'm learning so much from their feedback.
